Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: -Neutron Elastic Scattering Measurements At 7.0 Mev.-

x4freetext: ENTRY 20162, OTHER NUCL. AND ENERG. FROM AE-430 CDD IN
STUDSVIK 6 MEV VAN DE GRAAFF, PULSED,
(2NS AT A REPETITION RATE OF 1 MHZ), KLYSTRON BUNCHING
DISTANCE BETWEEN SAMPLE AND DETECTOR = 350 CM.
SCINTILLATOR NE213, 12.5 CM DIAM. AND 5 CM
NEUTRON FLUX WAS MONITORED WITH A LONG
OUTER DIAMETER AND 0.65 CM INNER DIAMETER.
- NEUTRON MULTIPLE SCATTERING IN THE SAMPLE,
- THE GEOMETRICAL EFFECT CAUSED BY THE SIZE OF THE
SAMPLE AND ITS DISTANCE FROM TARGET AND DETECTOR
WHERE DONE BY A MONTE CARLO PROGRAM,
.EXPERIMENTAL CROSS SECTION ERRORS ARE BETTER THAN 10
.STATISTICAL ERROR IN GENERAL BETTER THAN 2 PER-CENT,
EXCEPT IN THE MINIMA OF THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION WHERE
